text.section:
The University of Maryland School of Nursing and the Advisory Board shall ensure that the following geographic areas are served by the Program:
Western Maryland;
The Washington metropolitan area;
The Baltimore metropolitan area;
Southern/Central Maryland;
The upper Eastern Shore; and
The lower Eastern Shore.

section.section:
On or before September 1 of each year, the University of Maryland School of Nursing and the Advisory Board shall submit a report to the Governor and, in accordance with § 2-1246 of the State Government Article, the General Assembly detailing the operation and management of the Program, including:
The number of individuals served by the Program;
The type and number of health care services provided to individuals served by the Program;
The establishment and continuation of any public or private partnerships;
The funding received from public and private sources;
Funds received through third party reimbursement;
The condition and maintenance expenses of vehicles used by the Program to deliver health care services;
The areas served by the Program;
The impact of the Program in the communities served; and
Any recommendations for enhancing or furthering the purposes of the Program.
